article.headline: Cal St.-Fullerton 91, E. Washington 76
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Isiah Umipig had 25 points as all five Cal State Fullerton starters scored in double figures in a 91-76 victory against Eastern Washington on Sunday. Umipig made six 3-pointers for the Titans (6-3). Omondi Amoke and Orane Chin had 19 points each, Kwame Vaughn 12 and D.J. Seeley 10. Collin Chiverton scored 26 points and Cliff Colimon 23 for the Eagles (5-4). Amoke had 12 rebounds. Cal State Fullerton got permanent separation midway through the first half with a 20-4 run over a 4:18 stretch. Vaughn hit two 3-pointers, and Umipig and Seeley added one each during the surge, which gave the Titans a 30-15 lead.
